# General rules for MotherFluxer project

- You can @ files here
- You can use markdown but dont have to
- Always use functional React components
- Follow the MotherFluxer project structure from the documentation
- Format code according to project conventions
- Use TypeScript for type safety

# Database Conventions
- Follow the auth_service schema structure
- Use PostgreSQL best practices for queries
- Implement proper error handling for database operations

# Security Practices
- Always use proper JWT authentication
- Implement rate limiting as defined in the specs
- Follow AWS security best practices

# React Component Guidelines
- Use shadcn/ui components when available
- Only use Tailwind's core utility classes (no arbitrary values)
- Components should be self-contained and reusable

# Code Quality
- Implement proper error handling using the defined error classes
- Follow the established logging patterns
- Write comprehensive tests for new features

# AWS Infrastructure
- Follow the defined VPC configuration
- Use proper IAM roles and permissions
- Implement proper security group rules